Zafis has been around the lower East side for at least 30 years. They offer classic diner choices, from egg, pancake and French toast selections, to Brisket and roast turkey sandwiches and platters, with delicious gravy to go with it. Daily soup specials (the spilt pea or chicken rice or matzo ball soups are delicious)! The hamburgers are always done as asked and the service is quick. They even have diner specials and if you are a meatloaf fan, you have to try their spin on it. It's really good. They also offer wraps of many varieties. Service is Always quick and friendly and staff is very attentive. They are a bit pricey, but as my mother once told me....you get what you pay for! Also, the place, including the restrooms, are always very clean.
